h3. Problem Definition
If there's no Service Desk project created in JIRA, user will see a message below when viewing the Help Center. The message is misleading sometimes.
{quote}
h3. Welcome to the Help Center
It looks like you don't have access to this Help Center. If possible, please try contacting us another way.
{quote}

h3. Suggested Solution
Instead of a message sounding like a permission issue, please indicate the real problem i.e. no Service Desk project found.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-4133].
  {panel}

h3. Problem Definition

Currently when navigating to requests at customer portal, the default values for drop down menus are Created by me, Open requests and any request type.
For some use cases it would be great to be able to change the default value of the fields. So, when navigating to Requests page to have Any Status instead of Open Requests.

