Currently, a user who administers a Service Desk project consumes an Agent license.  Many Atlassian customers use the max of their licensed agents for normal daily work.  When a JIRA System Administrator is called in to help the team with Service Desk configuration or troubleshooting, that sysadmin does not have the proper permissions to assist the team.  There are also no Agent licenses available for the System Administrator to use (albeit temporarily) to assist the team either.  It would be great if those users with the global permission of System Administrator could configure a Service Desk, without consuming an Agent license.  

This is meant to be for troubleshooting purposes, or system problems which need to be worked quickly, and having the ability will help the sysadmin work the issue without worrying about lack of permissions. Thank you for your consideration.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
